## 9. Cross-Agent Pointer Pattern

`CLAUDE.md`, `GEMINI.md`, `AGENT.md` (if present in repo root) are
either:

- **Symlinks** with the relative target `AGENTS.md` (same directory),
  or
- **One-line pointer files** containing the literal text `@AGENTS.md`
  followed by a newline (the `@` prefix is the import syntax Claude
  Code and Gemini CLI resolve mechanically; a legacy bare `AGENTS.md`
  line is also treated as a pointer).

Both forms are valid. Agents reading their own runtime file should
resolve the pointer and load `AGENTS.md`. **Never duplicate content
across the alias files** — that is the failure mode this pattern
exists to prevent.

