## 10. Doc Update Routing

| Change | Update |
|---|---|
| Product / scope shift | `project_requirements.md` |
| Architecture decision | `decisions.md` (append) |
| Session handoff | `handoff/current_handoff.md` (replace) |
| Task completion | `coordination/work_queue.md` (one line; detail in commit) |
| Plan delta | `plans.md` (mark landed; demote to done) |
| User-facing setup | `README.md` |

Update docs **in the same commit** as the change. A change without a
doc update rots within two sessions.

**`README.md` vs `AGENTS.md`.** `README.md` is the human's entry
point: quickstart, install, run, debug addresses + ports, deploy
steps — optimize for clone-and-run-in-5-minutes. `AGENTS.md` (this
file) is the agent's entry point: routing, hard rules, working
principles. Same project, two audiences, no content overlap. For
README style inspiration, see
<https://github.com/matiassingers/awesome-readme>.

